modules.description: This module implements a WebSocket client that connects to a remote server using Eio for asynchronous networking. It provides functions to establish a connection with a custom configuration, handle incoming WebSocket messages, and manage connection lifecycle events. The module works with stream sockets and handles errors and incoming data through provided callbacks.

Handles WebSocket connections by creating a connection handler that processes incoming streams and WebSocket data. It works with network addresses, WebSocket descriptors, and input handlers to manage client communication. This module is used to implement custom WebSocket logic, such as message routing or real-time data exchange, within an Eio-based server.

This module implements WebSocket communication using Eio for asynchronous networking, with a server component that handles incoming connections and client communication, and a client component that connects to remote servers. It works with network addresses, stream sockets, and WebSocket descriptors to manage message exchange and connection lifecycle. Concrete use cases include real-time messaging systems, live data updates, and bidirectional communication protocols.
